@startuml nav_route_class_to_highway_ready_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Nav Route Class To Highway Ready Signal Flow\n(NAV route class + cruise/attention -> FCAM/HWP readiness)

participant "NAV / cruise /\ndriver attention inputs" as NavCtx #F4F7FB
participant "FCAM / HWP\nhighway readiness consumers" as PilotOwners #E8F7E8
participant "Highway pilot /\nlane-model outputs" as PilotBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / panels" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Route / Attention Inputs ==

NavCtx -> PilotOwners : gNavRouteClass\ngCruiseState\ngAttentionLevel\npathReady / laneGuideState
PilotOwners -> PilotOwners : FCAM laneModelValid =\n(pathReady and navRouteClass in {2,3})
PilotOwners -> PilotOwners : HWP highwayReady =\n(navRouteClass == 2 and cruiseState >= 1 and attentionLevel <= 2)
note right of PilotOwners
Representative gating inputs
- navRouteClass
- cruiseState
- attentionLevel
- pathReady / laneGuideState
end note

== Readiness Publish ==

PilotOwners -> PilotBus : frmFcamInputMsg\nLaneModelValid
PilotOwners -> PilotBus : frmHighwayPilotStateMsg\nHighwayPilotReady / LongCtrlActive / LatCtrlActive
note right of PilotOwners
Representative outputs
- LaneModelValid
- HighwayPilotReady
- LongCtrlActive / LatCtrlActive
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

PilotBus -> Obs : highway-ready / lane-model /\npilot-state readback

note over NavCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. NAV route class and vehicle attention context reach FCAM/HWP
2. FCAM validates lane model from route class and path readiness
3. HWP raises highway-ready when cruise and attention conditions fit
4. Pilot-state outputs expose readiness to downstream observers
end note

@enduml
